          "text": "While the commit is running through validation, let me summarize the fix:\n\n## Fix Summary for Issue #786\n\n**Problem**: When an account `check` directive fails in an included file, the warning reported the file/line of the `include` directive (or the triggering transaction), not the actual account directive location.\n\n**Root Cause**: In `src/xact.cc:1395`, the `check` path called `context.warning()`, which uses `parse_context_t::location()` — the *current parse context's* file/line. During transaction processing, this points to wherever the triggering transaction was being parsed, not the account directive's origin. In contrast, the `assert` path (which throws) correctly picks up the `auto_xact_t`'s own `pos` field via `item_context(*this, ...)` in the catch block.\n\n**Fix**: Replace `context.warning(...)` with a direct call to `warning_func(...)` that uses the `auto_xact_t`'s `pos->pathname` and `pos->beg_line` for the location string, falling back to `context.location()` if `pos` is not set.\n\n**Files changed**:\n- `src/xact.cc` — the one-line code fix\n- `test/regress/786.test` + `test/regress/786.dat` — new regression test with include\n- 8 existing test baselines updated to expect the corrected (directive) line numbers",
